HEADWORD: Insalivation
<hw>In*sal`i*va"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The mixing of the food with the saliva and
other secretions of the mouth in eating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insalubrious</ent>⟦br⟧
